-- Hungary Reacts ‘Constructively’ to Criticism, Jagland Tells FAZ
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-03-21T17:57:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/hungary-reacts-constructively-to-criticism-jagland-tells-faz.html
Council of Europe Secretary-General
Thorbjoern Jagland said Hungarian Prime Minister  Viktor Orban 
has reacted “very constructively” to its criticism of the
country’s justice reform,  Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung 
reported in a preview of a story that will run tomorrow.  Jagland said that “we’re on the right track” after
meeting Orban March 21, the newspaper reported, citing Jagland.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
